  <div class="lesson-content-body col-xs-12 ">

      <ul>
          <li>A photon is a particle of electromagnetic radiation (light, X-rays etc.)</li>  
          <li>Compton X-ray Scattering (or the 'Compton Effect') is the redirection of an X-ray photon
              by an electron.</li>          
          <li>Energy is transferred from the X-ray photon to the electron.</li>
        <li> The Compton effect is important in the treatment of cancers by radiotherapy.</li>
      </ul>
     
